Implement Phase 51: Full zDash Monorepo Import into zeaz-platform.

Primary repo:
- cvsz/zeaz-platform

Source repo:
- cvsz/zdash

Goal:
Move/merge/combine/integrate the full cvsz/zdash application repository into cvsz/zeaz-platform because zeaz-platform is the Cloudflare operator/control-plane for zeaz.dev.

Target architecture:
- zDash application code lives under apps/zdash/
- zeaz-platform root remains the Cloudflare operator, DNS/Tunnel/Access/IaC, free/no-cost guardrail, and release orchestration repo.
- zDash must remain runnable and testable from apps/zdash.
- Root Makefile must provide wrapper targets for zDash.

Hard rules:
- Preserve all zDash safety invariants.
- Preserve zeaz-platform free/no-cost defaults:
  - CLOUDFLARE_PLAN_TIER=Free
  - COST_LOCK=true
  - ALLOW_PAID_CLOUDFLARE_FEATURES=false
  - ALLOW_R2_WRITE=false
  - ALLOW_WORKERS_DEPLOY=false
  - ALLOW_LOAD_BALANCING=false
  - ALLOW_ADVANCED_WAF=false
  - ALLOW_LOGPUSH=false
- Do not enable live trading, real broker orders, real IoT actions, real social posting, destructive automation, Workers deployment, paid WAF, Load Balancing, Logpush, or R2 writes by default.
- No .env files tracked.
- No secrets printed.
- No Global API Key usage.
- All Cloudflare apply actions must remain dry-run unless explicitly confirmed.

Implementation plan:

1. Import zDash into apps/zdash
Use git subtree or equivalent safe import:
- Add remote named zdash-source pointing to git@github.com:cvsz/zdash.git or https://github.com/cvsz/zdash.git.
- Fetch main.
- Import into apps/zdash preserving history if possible.
- Do not use git submodule.
- Do not copy .git directory.
- Do not import runtime files, .env, node_modules, .venv, dist, .runtime, coverage, caches, or secret files.
- If apps/zdash already exists, update it safely and do not overwrite local uncommitted operator files.

2. Root Makefile wrappers
Add root targets:
- zdash-install
- zdash-validate
- zdash-validate-fast
- zdash-backend-test
- zdash-frontend-test
- zdash-build
- zdash-server-start
- zdash-server-stop
- zdash-server-restart
- zdash-server-status
- zdash-release-evidence
- zdash-phase48-validate
- zdash-cloudflare-handoff
- phase51-validate

Each target must cd apps/zdash and call the correct zDash target/script.
Root targets must fail safely if apps/zdash is missing.

3. Root docs
Create:
- docs/architecture/ZDASH_MONOREPO_INTEGRATION.md
- docs/runbooks/ZDASH_MONOREPO_OPERATIONS.md
- docs/reports/PHASE51_ZDASH_MONOREPO_IMPORT_REPORT.md

Docs must explain:
- zDash app now lives under apps/zdash
- zeaz-platform remains Cloudflare operator
- deployment responsibility split
- local dev commands
- CI commands
- Cloudflare route ownership
- rollback plan
- how to sync future zDash changes
- why submodule is not used

4. Cloudflare operator integration
Create or update:
- configs/cloudflare/zdash/zdash.edge.routes.example.json
- configs/cloudflare/zdash/zdash-dns-intent.example.json
- configs/cloudflare/zdash/zdash-access-policy.example.json
- generated/cloudflare/zdash-tunnel-ingress.yml

Keep all generated configs dry-run/example by default.

5. Scripts
Create:
- scripts/zdash/import-zdash-subtree.sh
- scripts/zdash/sync-zdash-subtree.sh
- scripts/zdash/verify-zdash-monorepo.sh
- scripts/zdash/run-zdash-validation.sh
- scripts/zdash/capture-zdash-monorepo-evidence.sh

Script requirements:
- executable
- bash strict mode
- no secrets printed
- safe failure messages
- no force push
- no destructive deletion
- do not require Cloudflare secrets
- validate apps/zdash exists
- validate zDash backend/frontend folders exist
- validate zDash Makefile exists
- validate no nested .git exists under apps/zdash
- validate no .env tracked

6. CI
Create or update:
- .github/workflows/zdash-monorepo.yml

Workflow must:
- run on push and pull_request
- not require secrets
- validate apps/zdash exists
- run root phase51-validate
- optionally run zDash validate-fast if dependency install is available
- upload evidence artifact if generated
- never print secrets

7. README update
Update root README.md:
- Add "Integrated applications" section.
- List apps/zdash.
- Explain zDash is now integrated under zeaz-platform.
- Keep existing Cloudflare free/no-cost guardrails.
- Add commands:
  - make zdash-validate-fast
  - make zdash-server-start
  - make phase51-validate

8. Release evidence
Create:
- docs/releases/zdash/ZDASH_MONOREPO_IMPORT_EVIDENCE.md
- docs/reports/generated/zdash-monorepo-evidence.md

Include:
- source repo
- target path
- imported commit SHA placeholder
- validation status
- safety status
- no-secret status
- rollback command notes

9. Rollback plan
Document:
- git revert import commit
- remove apps/zdash only through revert, not rm -rf
- disable Cloudflare route intent
- keep original cvsz/zdash repo read-only until final migration accepted
- do not delete original repo until CI and deployment are stable

10. Validation
phase51-validate must check:
- apps/zdash exists
- apps/zdash/backend exists
- apps/zdash/frontend exists
- apps/zdash/Makefile exists
- no apps/zdash/.git directory
- no tracked .env files
- no obvious secret-looking values in generated evidence
- root README mentions apps/zdash
- root Makefile has zdash wrapper targets
- Cloudflare zDash route configs exist
- monorepo docs/reports exist

Acceptance criteria:
- Full zDash repo is present under apps/zdash.
- Root zeaz-platform can operate zDash through Makefile wrappers.
- Cloudflare operator configs for zDash are under zeaz-platform.
- No submodule.
- No nested .git.
- No tracked .env.
- No secrets.
- phase51-validate passes.
- Existing zeaz-platform validation still passes.
